The paper deals with complexity measures of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper specifically focuses on sensitivity and block sensitivity, which are measures related to decision trees and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions certificate complexity, which is a measure related to information theory (cs.IT). The techniques used in the paper involve probabilistic arguments and combinatorial analysis, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
